BRUSSELS, March 28 (Reuters) - Eurojust, the EU Agency for criminal justice cooperation, said on Monday it supported the creation of a joint investigation team (JIT) into alleged war crimes committed in Ukraine. "The responsible national authorities of Lithuania, Poland and Ukraine signed a JIT agreement on 25 March to enable the exchange of information and facilitate investigations into war crimes, crimes against humanity and other core crimes," Eurojust said in a statement. Our Standards: The Thomson Reuters Trust Principles.